<paragraph blockId="87.[189,1399,1891,2025]" lastBlockId="88.[189,1399,266,363]" lastPageId="88" lastPageNumber="89" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">
<taxonomicName authority="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin, 2018" authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[189,630,1891,1917]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granditarsis" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis box="[189,630,1891,1917]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Sphegina (Asiosphegina) granditarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[636,725,1891,1917]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin, 2018" authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[871,1068,1891,1918]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atrimanus" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis box="[871,1068,1891,1918]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">S. (A.) atrimanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1073,1165,1891,1917]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin, 2018" authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[1175,1399,1891,1918]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incretonigra" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis box="[1175,1399,1891,1918]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">S. (A.) incretonigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[189,285,1927,1953]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hippa, van Steenis &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2015" box="[299,465,1927,1954]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nasuta" subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis box="[299,465,1927,1954]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">S. (A.) nasuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin, 2018" authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[482,715,1927,1954]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrotarsata" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis box="[482,715,1927,1954]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">S. (A.) nigrotarsata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[725,818,1927,1953]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<emphasis box="[881,1088,1927,1954]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kertesz" authorityYear="1914" box="[881,1084,1927,1954]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orientalis" subGenus="Asiosphegina">S. (A.) orientalis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Except for the characters mentioned in the key 
<taxonomicName authority="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin, 2018" authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[450,678,1963,1990]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granditarsis" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis box="[450,678,1963,1990]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">S. (A.) granditarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[687,780,1963,1989]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from the other mentioned species by having only very sparse pile posteriorly on male sternum IV. The male genitalia are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kertesz" authorityYear="1914" box="[189,384,266,293]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="88" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orientalis" subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis box="[189,204,267,293]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[219,246,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">(A</emphasis>
.
<emphasis box="[254,384,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">) orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the dorsal lobe of surstylus is not widened on the apical part and the ventral lobe is pointed, not obtuse. Moreover, the long seta-like pile on the cercus is much longer. See also under 
<taxonomicName authority="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin, 2018" authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[189,389,336,363]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atrimanus" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis box="[189,389,336,363]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">S. (A.) atrimanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[397,487,336,362]" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="88" pageNumber="89" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="88.[189,324,401,427]" box="[189,324,401,427]" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,401,427]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,401,427]" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="88.[189,1399,448,509]" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">
The specific epithet is from the Latin ‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[636,779,448,474]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granditarsis">
<emphasis box="[636,779,448,474]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">granditarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’, meaning ‘having a large tarsus’ and referring to the enlarged and flattened protarsus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
